22 B. 1. The redbud school grants shall be determined by the
23 State Department of Education as follows:
24
ENGR. S. B. NO. 346 Page 15

1 a. divide the county four-mill levy revenue by four to
2 determine the nonchargeable county four-mill revenue
3 for each school district,
4 b. determine the amount of new revenue generated by the
5 five-mill building fund levy as authorized by Section
6 10 of Article X of the Oklahoma Constitution for each
7 school district as reported in the Oklahoma Cost
8 Accounting System for the preceding fiscal year,
9 c. add the amounts calculated in subparagraphs a and b of
10 this paragraph to determine the nonchargeable millage
11 for each school district,
12 d. add the nonchargeable millage in each district
13 statewide as calculated in subparagraph c of this
14 paragraph and divide the total by the average daily
15 membership in public schools statewide based on the
16 preceding school year’s average daily membership,
17 according to the provisions of Section 18-107 of this
18 title. This amount is the statewide nonchargeable
19 millage per student, known as the baseline local
20 funding per student,
21 e. all eligible charter schools shall be included in
22 these calculations as unique school districts,
23 separate from the school district that may sponsor the
24 eligible charter school, and the total number of
ENGR. S. B. NO. 346 Page 16

1 districts shall be used to determine the statewide
2 average baseline local funding per student,
3 f. for each school district or eligible charter school
4 which is below the baseline local funding per student,
5 the Department shall subtract the baseline local
6 funding per student from the average nonchargeable
7 millage per student of the school district or eligible
8 charter school to determine the nonchargeable millage
9 per student shortfall for each district, and
10 g. the nonchargeable millage per student shortfall for a
11 school district or eligible charter school shall be
12 multiplied by the average daily membership of the
13 preceding school year of the eligible school district
14 or eligible charter school. This amount shall be the
15 redbud school grant amount for the school district or
16 eligible charter school.
17 2. For fiscal year 2022, monies for the redbud school grants
18 shall be expended from the funds apportioned pursuant to Section 426
19 of Title 63 of the Oklahoma Statutes. For fiscal year 2023 and each
20 subsequent fiscal year, monies for the redbud school grants shall be
21 appropriated pursuant to Section 426 of Title 63 of the Oklahoma
22 Statutes, not to exceed three-fourths (3/4) of the tax collected in
23 the preceding fiscal year pursuant to Section 426 of Title 63 of the
24 Oklahoma Statutes as determined by the Oklahoma Tax Commission. For
ENGR. S. B. NO. 346 Page 17

1 fisc al year 2023 and each subsequent fiscal year, if such
2 appropriated funds are insufficient to fund the redbud school
3 grants, then an additional apportionment of funds shall be made from
4 sales tax collections as provided by subsection D of Section 1353 of
5 Title 68 of the Oklahoma Statutes. If both funds are insufficient,
6 the Department shall promulgate rules to permit a decrease to the
7 baseline local funding per student to the highest amount allowed
8 with the funding available.
