10 subject of any allegation of inappropriate behavior with a student.
11 5. Any person employed as a full-time teacher by a school
12 district in this state for ten (10) or more consecutive years
13 immediately preceding an application for employment as a substitute
14 teacher in the same school district may not be required to have a
15 national criminal history record check for as long as the person
16 remains employed for consecutive years by that school district as a
17 substitute teacher, if the teacher left full-time employment in good
18 standing. If the teacher applies for employment as a substitute
19 teacher in another school district, a national criminal history
20 record check shall be required.
21 G. 1. Except as otherwise provided by this subsection, any
22 teacher employed by an Oklahoma school district prior to May 19,
23 2020, who does not have an Oklahoma criminal history record check
24 from the Oklahoma State Bureau of Investigation as well as a
ENGR. S. B. NO. 346 Page 24

1 nati onal criminal history record check, as defined in Section 150.9
2 of Title 74 of the Oklahoma Statutes, on file with his or her
3 employing district as required by this section shall complete the
4 criminal history record checks upon the next renewal of his or her
5 standard teaching certificate as required by Section 6-154.1 of this
6 title or State Board of Education administrative rules promulgated
7 thereto.
8 2. Except as otherwise provided by this subsection, any other
9 person employed by an Oklahoma school district prior to May 19,
10 2020, who does not have an Oklahoma criminal history record check
11 from the Oklahoma State Bureau of Investigation as well as a
12 national criminal history record check, as defined in Section 150.9
13 of Title 74 of the Oklahoma Statutes, on file with his or her
14 employing district as required by this section shall have until July
15 1, 2022, to complete the criminal history record checks.
16 3. Any teacher eligible to retire from the Teachers’ Retirement
17 System of Oklahoma who does not have an Oklahoma criminal history
18 record check from the Oklahoma State Bureau of Investigation as well
19 as a national criminal history record check, as defined in Section
20 150.9 of Title 74 of the Oklahoma Statutes, on file with his or her
21 employing district as required by this section shall complete the
22 criminal history record checks by the earlier of the following
23 dates:
24 a. July 1, 2022, or
ENGR. S. B. NO. 346 Page 25

1 b. at the next renewal of his or her standard teaching
2 certificate as required by Section 6-154.1 of this
3 title or State Board of Education administrative rules
4 promulgated thereto.
5 H. Any person who willfully submits an affidavit required by
6 paragraphs 1 and 3 of subsection F of this section which the person
7 knows to be false shall, upon conviction, be guilty of a misdemeanor
8 punishable by imprisonment in the county jail for not more than one
9 (1) year, or by a fine not more than Five Hundred Dollars ($500.00),
10 or by both such imprisonment and fine.
11 I. A board of education shall be prohibited from hiring a full-
12 time teacher who fails to provide the affidavit required by
13 paragraphs 1 and 3 of subsection F of this section.
14 J. The provisions of this section shall not apply to technology
15 center employees hired on a part-time or temporary basis for the
16 instruction of adult students only.
17 I. K. The provisions of this section shall not apply to law
18 enforcement officers who are employed by an employing agency at the
19 time of application for employment at a public school district.
20 J. L. Nothing in this section shall be construed to impose
21 liability on school districts, except in negligence, for employing
22 prospective employees within the sixty-day temporary employment
23 window pending the results of the national criminal history record
24 check.
